President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Confederated Tribes of the Colville Reservation and authorized federal aid to support their efforts in areas affected by flooding from May 5 to May 28, 2018. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy B. Manner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.